  "prompt": "How do I remove the Google Docs header while sharing a file?",
  "response": "Google Docs does not provide a direct way to remove the header while sharing the file itself. However, you can accomplish the goal by removing the header before sharing the document. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to remove the header in Google Docs:\n\n1. **Open your Google Docs document**: Go to Google Docs (https://docs.google.com/) and open the document from which you want to remove the header.\n\n2. **Access the header**: Double-click on the header area or click on the `Insert` menu, then select `Header and page number` \u2192 `Header`.\n\n3. **Remove the header content**: Click inside the header area. Press the `Backspace` or `Delete` key to remove any text or images in the header.\n\n4. **Close the header**: To exit the header, click anywhere outside the header area, or simply press `Esc` on your keyboard.\n\n5. **Sharing the document**: After removing the header, you can share the document. Click the blue `Share` button at the top right corner of the document. Specify the individuals you want to share the document with, or obtain a shareable link.\n\nBy removing the header before sharing, the recipients will not see the header content. If you need to retain the header for your own use but not share it, you may consider making a copy of the document, removing the header from the copy, and then sharing that copy.\n\nRemember to re-enable or re-add the header if you need it for your own purposes after sharing.",
